## BACKLOG-019 - Define ticket traceability model and schema path
- Status: Grooming
- Owner: Paula Product
- Requester: current session
- Date added: 2026-04-13
- Updated: 2026-04-14T08:53:03.000Z
- Due Date: 
- Priority: P1
- Effort: 2
- Sprint Assigned: 
- Ready for Implementation?: No
- Tech handoff owner: Unassigned
- Summary: Define the traceability source of truth and decide whether the current backlog schema is sufficient or needs a controlled migration path.
- Outcome / user value: Product and engineering can plan traceability as a small set of clear outcomes instead of carrying one overloaded parent request into sprint work.
- Scope notes: In scope, keeping the traceability epic grouped into child stories for source of truth, ticket UI behavior, workflow ownership, and legacy backlog handling. In scope, deciding whether traceability should stay fully integration-derived or whether a schema change is justified, plus defining migration expectations for existing templates and backlog files if that schema change is approved. Out of scope, making ad hoc schema edits without a documented migration path or keeping unresolved parent-level planning work assigned to the active sprint.
- Acceptance criteria:
  - [ ] The traceability work is grouped into smaller stories with one primary outcome each.
  - [ ] The child stories clearly cover source of truth, ticket UI behavior, workflow ownership, and older backlog handling.
  - [ ] The dependency order makes it clear which child stories can move independently to `Ready` and which ones still need product or workflow decisions.
  - [ ] The story explicitly states whether the existing markdown schema remains sufficient or a schema change is required for traceability.
  - [ ] If a schema change is required, the story defines a controlled migration expectation for existing templates and backlog files on first load in a later version.
  - [ ] Sprint-ready implementation work is tracked on child stories instead of this parent coordination card.
- Dependencies: BACKLOG-020, BACKLOG-021, BACKLOG-022, BACKLOG-023.
- Links: current session request
- Implementation notes: Product direction updated to allow a schema change if traceability cannot be supported cleanly through integration-derived metadata alone, but only with an explicit migration path and prompt guidance for later-version first-load migration.

