### Epic 6, Board switching and numeric selector hygiene

## BACKLOG-039 - Warn before switching projects during active Paula work
- Status: Done
- Owner: Paula Product
- Requester: current session
- Date added: 2026-04-14
- Updated: 2026-04-14T08:56:15Z
- Due Date: 
- Priority: P1
- Effort: 1
- Sprint Assigned: Sprint 7
- Ready for Implementation?: Yes
- Tech handoff owner: Ben
- Summary: Show a clear warning before users switch projects while Paula is actively working on the current board.
- Outcome / user value: Users can avoid interrupting or abandoning active grooming work by mistake when they switch to another project.
- Scope notes: In scope, detecting an active Paula session at project-switch time, presenting a confirmation warning before the switch completes, and making the consequence legible in plain language. In scope, allowing the user to either stay on the current project or continue with the switch after confirmation. Out of scope, redesigning Paula session management, preserving one Paula run across projects, or introducing a hard block that prevents all switching.
- Acceptance criteria:
  - [ ] If Paula is actively working on the current board, initiating a project switch shows a warning before the switch completes.
  - [ ] The warning states that Paula is still working on the current project and that switching projects may interrupt that backlog session.
  - [ ] The warning offers a clear stay action and a clear continue-switch action.
  - [ ] Choosing the stay action leaves the user on the current project with the active Paula session unchanged.
  - [ ] Choosing the continue-switch action completes the project switch without showing the warning again during the same user action.
  - [ ] If Paula is not actively working, the project switch continues without showing the warning.
- Dependencies: BACKLOG-002, project switch flow, Paula active-session state.
- Links: current session request
- Implementation notes: Added a project-switch confirmation overlay that appears only when the active Paula session is attached to the current backlog, with explicit Stay here and Continue switch actions. Build passed.

