- Outcome / user value: Users can return to the same board setup without rebuilding their preferred filters and sort order every time.
- Scope notes: In scope, one visible action beside filters and sorting that stores the current filter and sort state for the current user and restores it on the next visit. Out of scope, multiple named saved views, shared team views, dashboards, or markdown mutations.
- Acceptance criteria:
  - [ ] A `Save layout` button appears beside the filter and sorting controls.
  - [ ] Activating the button stores the user's current filter and sort selections without mutating the markdown source.
  - [ ] When the same user returns later, the board restores the last saved filter and sort selections automatically.
  - [ ] The saved layout applies only to the current user and does not affect other users.
- Dependencies: Board filtering model, sort-state persistence, per-user preference storage.
- Links: local UX backlog
- Implementation notes: Implemented as a per-user localStorage layout save and restore beside the existing filter controls.

